{"itemid":584,"subject":"Locus Awards Shortlist","event":"LOCUS has announced the shortlist for its annual awards, and I'm pleased to report that SONGS OF THE DYING EARTH, the Jack Vance tribute anthology I co-edited with Gardner Dozois, has been nominated in the Best Anthology category.\r\n\r\n((Three of the five nominees in Best Anthology were edited or co-edited by Gardner, who is also up himself in the Best Editor category.  Despite which, he is convinced he is going to lose both awards.   That's why we call him Eeyore.))\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://pics.livejournal.com/grrm/pic/0003q6se/\"><img src=\"http://pics.livejournal.com/grrm/pic/0003q6se/s320x240\" width=\"158\" height=\"240\" border='0'/></a>\r\n\r\nNeil Gaimain's story for SONGS OF THE DYING EARTH is also a finalist, in Best Short Story, and Vance's autobiography has been nominated in Best Related Book.\r\n\r\nFor the full list, check here: http://www.locusmag.com/News/2010/04/locus-awards-finalists.html","ditemid":149558,"eventtime":"2010-04-20 16:45:00","props":{"personifi_word_count":131,"taglist":"anthologies, dying earth","opt_screening":"F","current_moodid":109,"commentalter":1271972167,"interface":"web","personifi_tags":"17:5,6:11,16:5,3:70,4:70,20:11,22:11,nterms:yes"},"can_comment":0,"logtime":"2010-04-20 22:45:27","anum":54,"url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html","event_timestamp":1271781900,"reply_count":9,"comments":[{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/111240558/12467186","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?replyto=9747510","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?thread=9747510#t9747510","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?thread=9747510#t9747510","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?thread=9747510#t9747510","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"saladinahmed","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://saladinahmed.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":9747510,"talkid":38076,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?thread=9747510#t9747510","upictitle":"saladinahmed: pic#111240558","article":"It's a *great* antho, and certainly deserves the nod.  Though to be honest I had to read a pal's copy b/c the hardcovers are now going for like $100 on Amazon right now, and, well, I gots mouths to feed over here :)  <br /><br />Will it be out in trade paperback at all?  I'd like to own it.<br /><br />In general, a lot of great stuff in most categories on the Locus list.  The fact that DJA's Price of Spring didn't make the fantasy novel cut, though, kind of drives me batshit.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"7 years ago","ctime":"April 20 2010, 22:57:29 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://saladinahmed.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"saladinahmed","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"saladinahmed","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://saladinahmed.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"saladinahmed","ctime_ts":1271804249,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?replyto=9749814","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?thread=9749814#t9749814","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?thread=9749814#t9749814","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/149558.html?thread=97498